    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2189965432" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2189965432" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3743145-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1519762773p2/3743145.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2189965432?book_show_action=true">Sep 17, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/3743145-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316065795" href="/book/show/7806618-the-swan-thieves">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">fans of Possession and The Last Painting of Sara de Vos</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=2019-read">2019-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=5-star">5-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=new-york">new-york</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=loved-it">loved-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=paris">paris</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=cover-me-black">cover-me-black</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=top-10-2019">top-10-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3743145-kelly?shelf=art">art</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2189965432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8041523593846572065">4.5 stars<br/><br/>This book got under my skin. It was beautifully written, with echoes between past and present rendered delicately, wonderfully, throughout the story. Obsession, theft, possession, and then the eyebrow-raising love between Impressionist artists Olivier and Beatrice echoed in the spring-autumn love of <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[Andrew and Mary <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> and even, to some degree, between Henri and Aude.<br/><br/>It&apos;s a very slow burn, but I had the time to read it for hours on end across several days and </span>
  <span id="freeText8041523593846572065" style="display:none">4.5 stars<br /><br />This book got under my skin. It was beautifully written, with echoes between past and present rendered delicately, wonderfully, throughout the story. Obsession, theft, possession, and then the eyebrow-raising love between Impressionist artists Olivier and Beatrice echoed in the spring-autumn love of <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Andrew and Mary <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> and even, to some degree, between Henri and Aude.<br /><br />It's a very slow burn, but I had the time to read it for hours on end across several days and to immerse myself in each narrative. Reading through these pages was like watching a painting slowly emerge on a canvas. Kostova strokes, with intelligence and patience, delicate brushes of enlightenment across the centuries of this mystery. She is a master and this is a masterpiece.<br /><br />I also loved the immensely talented Kostova's first book, <i>The Historian</i>. Both stories are unforgettable. Like <i>The Historian</i>, this book is also meandering, but perhaps more measured and mature.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8041523593846572065" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


