    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_231363157" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/231363157" />
    <a title="Sheila" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6810645-sheila"><img alt="Sheila" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1460570342p2/6810645.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/231363157?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sheila" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sheila" href="/user/show/6810645-sheila">Sheila</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316065795" href="/book/show/7806618-the-swan-thieves">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6810645-sheila?shelf=read-in-2019">read-in-2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer231363157" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14678224633844354104">5 stars--amazing. <br/><br/>Reviews for this book are mixed, and I understand why--there&apos;s not much plot. This is a dual-timeline historical novel with emphasis on characterization. Not a lot happens, and if you&apos;re expecting a thriller, 500+ pages of non-action would seem dull. I greatly enjoyed Kostova&apos;s first book (<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30236962.The_Historian' title='The Historian by Elizabeth Kostova' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Historian</a>) as well, though the same complaints (&quot;slow,&quot; &quot;boring&quot;) are also (understandably!) leveled at it.<br/><br/>I, however, loved the quietness of the characters, the exquisite writing, and th</span>
  <span id="freeText14678224633844354104" style="display:none">5 stars--amazing. <br /><br />Reviews for this book are mixed, and I understand why--there's not much plot. This is a dual-timeline historical novel with emphasis on characterization. Not a lot happens, and if you're expecting a thriller, 500+ pages of non-action would seem dull. I greatly enjoyed Kostova's first book (<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/30236962.The_Historian" title="The Historian by Elizabeth Kostova" rel="nofollow noopener">The Historian</a>) as well, though the same complaints ("slow," "boring") are also (understandably!) leveled at it.<br /><br />I, however, loved the quietness of the characters, the exquisite writing, and the slow reveal of the historical mystery. I really love plots that contain mysterious notes and hidden secrets, and the French art-world setting was perfect. My one wish is for more of Beatrice, whose life was central to the whole book, but who remained mysterious, despite her point-of-view chapters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14678224633844354104" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


